<refentry id="MGR-SETGTM">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>SET GTM</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>7</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo>Manage - Language Statements</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>SET GTM</refname>
    <refpurpose>change the value of parameter which is belong to the table of pg_settings</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <indexterm zone="mgr-setgtm">
    <primary>SET GTM</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>
SET GTM ALL ( { parameter = <replaceable class="parameter">value</replaceable> } [, ...] ) [ FORCE ]
SET GTM { MASTER | SLAVE | EXTRA } <replaceable class="parameter">node_name</replaceable> ( { parameter = <replaceable class="parameter">value</replaceable> } [, ...] ) [ FORCE ]

<phrase>where <replaceable class="parameter">Parameter</replaceable> can be one of:</phrase>

    the parameter that in the file of postgres.conf and alse belong to the table of pg_settings
    </synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>
SET GTM change the the value of parameter which is belong to the table of pg_settings and update param table, it won't check the the value and name of parameter correctly if adding 'force' at the tail of command line,in addition,it will update param table.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">Parameter</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            the parameter that in the file of postgres.conf
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>


  <refsect1>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <para>
      Change the the value of 'synchronous_commit' and 'max_wal_senders':
<programlisting>
set gtm master gtm_name1(synchronous_commit = off, max_wal_senders = 10);
</programlisting>
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>See Also</title>

    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member><xref linkend="mgr-resetgtm"></member>
    </simplelist>
  </refsect1>


</refentry>
